    <description>
      	<p>A fast, flurent, light weight music player written in GTK4.</p>

        <h3 id="toc_1.1">Features</h3>

        <ul dir="auto">
        <li>Supports most music file types,  samba or any other GIO supported remote protocols.</li>
        <li>Fast loading music files and parsing tags.</li>
        <li>Low memory / storage costs, no thumbnail caches.</li>
        <li>Gaussian blurred album cover as window background, follow GNOME 42 light/dark mode.</li>
        <li>Album cover with original resolution, can be exported.</li>
        <li>Flurent transition animations when switching songs and toogling play/pause.</li>
        <li>Supports full-text searching.</li>
        <li>Supports drag-drop from file manager.</li>
        <li>Supports pipewire audio sink.</li>
        <li>Show dynamic audio peak when playing.</li>
        </ul>

    </description>
        
